---
import SidebarLayout from '../../../layouts/SidebarLayout.astro';
import "../../../styles/global.css";
---

<SidebarLayout app="react">
  <h1 class="text-xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-5 text-custom-accent text-center">
    React Tutorials
  </h1>

  <section class="mb-5 space-y-6 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed text-custom-secondary">
    <p>
      <strong class="text-custom-primary">React</strong> is a popular JavaScript library for building user interfaces, particularly web applications. Developed by Facebook, React makes it painless to create interactive UIs.
    </p>

    <p>
      React uses a component-based architecture and a virtual DOM for efficient updates. It allows developers to build large web applications that can change data without reloading the page.
    </p>

    <p>
      In this tutorial series, you'll learn:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-4">
      <li>React components and JSX syntax</li>
      <li>Props and state management</li>
      <li>Event handling and forms</li>
      <li>React Hooks and functional components</li>
      <li>Component lifecycle and effects</li>
      <li>Routing and state management</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6 mt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mb-3">Why Learn React?</h2>
      <p>
        React is one of the most in-demand skills in web development. It's used by thousands of companies including Facebook, Instagram, Netflix, and Airbnb. React's component-based approach makes code reusable and maintainable.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        With a huge ecosystem and strong community support, React continues to evolve with new features and best practices that make building complex applications more efficient.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</SidebarLayout>